java.lang.Cloneable
public class VersionDeleteTask
extends MantisConnectTask

This task can be used to delete a project version via Ant.

The following attributes are mandatory:

  • url
  • username
  • password
  • project (The name of the project)
  • name (The name of the version to update)
  • failOnError (Indicates whether the build should fail if an error occures - defaults to true)
  • sessionClass: Classname for the Session to use. The class must implement org.mantisbt.connect.IMCSession and provide a public constructor with the following arguments:
    1. java.net.URL - URL
    2. java.lang.String - username
    3. java.lang.String - password
    4. java.lang.String - proxyHost
    5. int - proxyPort
    This attribute ist optional.

Example: 

     <taskdef name="deleteversion" classname="org.mantisbt.connect.ant.taskdefs.VersionDeleteTask" classpath="${cp}" />
     
     <target name="delete-version">
                <deleteversion url="http://yourhost/mantis/mc/mantisconnect.php"
                        username="AUser"
                        password="APassword"
                        project="AProjectName"
                        name="1.0.1"
                        failOnError="false"/>
     </target>

Peter Lanser, planser@users.sourceforge.net
